                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-174-victim1432 t18320517-174-viclabel1019"></join> to Lord Beverley, who lives in <placeName id="t18320517-174-crimeloc1020">Portman-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-174-crimeloc1020" type="placeName" value="Portman-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-174-crimeloc1020" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-174-off1017 t18320517-174-crimeloc1020"></join>. I missed two sovereigns out of a portmanteau in April, and then I missed some silver - the coachman then marked a sovereign and ten shillings, and I put them in the portmanteau from which I had lost the other money; I went to it at half-past eight o'clock the next morning, which was the 8th of May, and I missed a marked shilling and a marked sovereign from there; I asked the prisoner to lend me a shilling, which he did - I asked him to lend me another, which he did, and the second one was the marked shilling I had missed from the portmanteau; it must have been got by forcing open the portmanteau at one end of the lid.</p>
               <p>JAMES FRUIN. I am servant to Lord Beverley's eldest son. On the 8th of May the prisoner asked me for change for a sovereign, which I gave him - the sovereign I received from him I gave to the officer.</p>
               <p>
            
