             (Police-constable D 114). I took the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183205170094"></xptr>prisoner. I found on him ten shillings, three half-crowns and 2s. 6d.; I asked what he had done with the sovereign; he said he had got change from the servant in the house, and the servant produced the sovereign - I asked how he came to do this; he said he was going out of town with his master, and he had put his hand into the trunk and taken out the sovereign and the shilling, with an intention of returning them.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received an excellent character, and one witness engaged to employ him.</p>
